ion obligation, prior to the expiration of the Survival Period, provided, however, that no claim for breach of a representation or warranty of Seller shall be actionable or payable if the breach in question results from or is based on a condition, state of facts or other matter which was known to Purchaser prior to Closing, and unless the valid claims for all such breaches collectively aggregate more than Twenty-Five Thousand Dollars ($25,000.00), in which event, the full amount of such claims shall be actionable, subject to the cap on Seller’s Maximum Liability as hereinafter set forth.  Subject to the limitations set forth in the immediately preceding sentence, all remedies shall be those set forth in Section 16 below, and notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, Seller’s liability under any representation, warranty, covenant or indemnity made hereunder or in any of the Closing
 



  


